articularly in the LocalizationContext class. I wonder if moving the tests to a new LocaleSupportTest could preserve coverage while clarifying the structure. Balancing this change feels tricky!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Creating a Dedicated Test File**\\n\\nI'm considering creating a new dedicated test file that can include both localizationContext and LocaleSupport tests. The method `localizationContextAndLocaleSupportResolve` uses a direct LocalizationContext object, while `localeSupportLoadsBundleByBasename` covers line 309. I need to copy relevant bundles into the new LocaleSupportTest and remove them from the generic tests to maintain compliance. However, removing tests could reduce coverage of LocalizationContext. I just want to make sure everything aligns without losing necessary coverage. Balancing the structure feels essential!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_yHUvVlorVeAoTxO1WBfaJ7SO|fc_091fea2f9a7b3a89016a0bd3b4cd5c81a380c39d00f408b051", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/jakarta.servlet.jsp.jstl/jakarta.servlet.jsp.jstl-api/3.1.0-M1/src/test/java/jakarta_servlet_jsp_jstl/jakarta_servlet_jsp_jstl_api/LocaleSupportTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import java.util.ListResourceBundle;\n\nimport jakarta.servlet.jsp.PageContext;\nimport jakarta.servlet.jsp.jstl.core.Config;\nimport jakarta.servlet.jsp.jstl.fmt.LocaleSupport;\n", "newText": "import java.util.ListResourceBundle;\nimport java.util.Locale;\nimport java.util.ResourceBundle;\n\nimport jakarta.servlet.jsp.PageContext;\nimport jakarta.servlet.jsp.jstl.core.Config;\nimport jakarta.servlet.jsp.jstl.fmt.LocaleSupport;\nimport jakarta.servlet.jsp.jstl.fmt.LocalizationContext;\n"}, {"oldText": "public class LocaleSupportTest {\n    private static final String ROOT_MESSAGES_BUNDLE = \"jakarta_servlet_jsp_jstl.jakarta_servlet_jsp_jstl_api\"\n            + \".LocaleSupportTest$RootMessages\";\n\n    @Test\n    void loadsRootBundleWhenConfiguredLocaleDoesNotMatchAvailab